  "fullArabic": "وَإِنِ ٱمۡرَأَةٌ خَافَتۡ مِنۢ بَعۡلِهَا نُشُوزًا أَوۡ إِعۡرَاضٗا فَلَا جُنَاحَ عَلَيۡهِمَآ أَن يُصۡلِحَا بَيۡنَهُمَا صُلۡحٗاۚ وَٱلصُّلۡحُ خَيۡرٞۗ وَأُحۡضِرَتِ ٱلۡأَنفُسُ ٱلشُّحَّۚ وَإِن تُحۡسِنُواْ وَتَتَّقُواْ فَإِنَّ ٱللَّهَ كَانَ بِمَا تَعۡمَلُونَ خَبِيرٗا",
  "fullTranslation": "And if a woman fears from her husband contempt or evasion, there is no sin upon them if they make terms of settlement between them - and settlement is best. And present in [human] souls is stinginess. But if you do good and fear Allah - then indeed Allah is ever, with what you do, Acquainted.",
  "fullTransliteration": "wa-ini im'ra-atun khafat min ba'liha nushuzan aw i'radan fala junaha alayhima an yus'liha baynahuma sul'han wal-sul'hu khayrun wa-uh'dirati al-anfusu al-shuha wa-in tuh'sinu watattaqu fa-inna al-laha kana bima ta'maluna khabiran"
